# LionMesh TODO

This file tracks the next practical steps required to move LionMesh from prototype toward a credible field-tested MVP.

---

## 1. Project credibility

- [ ] Add `TODO.md` to the repository
- [ ] Add `STATUS.md`
- [ ] Add `TEST_RESULTS.md` once real tests have been performed
- [ ] Add screenshots of the WebApp to the README
- [ ] Clearly mark which parts are implemented, experimental, and planned
- [ ] Add a simple two-node setup guide
- [ ] Add a known limitations section

---

## 2. Minimal viable field setup

Goal: prove that LionMesh works with simple, reproducible hardware before extending the SDR layer.

Test setup:

- [ ] Raspberry Pi Node A
- [ ] Raspberry Pi Node B
- [ ] WiFi adapter on both nodes
- [ ] LoRa / Meshtastic device on both nodes
- [ ] GPS source on both nodes
- [ ] Battery or UPS power source
- [ ] WebApp reachable from at least one client device

Expected result:

- [ ] Node A can see Node B
- [ ] Node B can see Node A
- [ ] WebApp displays both nodes
- [ ] Basic mesh communication works
- [ ] System can run without internet

---

## 3. WiFi / batman-adv validation

The WiFi mesh mode should be treated as the first deployable LionMesh mode.

- [ ] Install and configure batman-adv on both nodes
- [ ] Assign static mesh IPs
- [ ] Confirm ping between nodes
- [ ] Measure latency
- [ ] Measure throughput with `iperf3`
- [ ] Test range with omni antennas
- [ ] Test range with improved antennas
- [ ] Document distance, antenna type, TX power and environment
- [ ] Add results to `TEST_RESULTS.md`

Minimum result to document:

```text
Mode: WiFi / batman-adv
Nodes: 2
Distance:
Antenna:
Throughput:
Latency:
Packet loss:
Environment:
Result:
